In the year 1333, the Kamakura shogunate government comes crumbling down. A trusted vassal, Ashikaga Takauji, betrays the shogunate and organizes a rebellion. Houjou Tokiyuki, the rightful heir, escapes the massacre with a Shinto priest named Suwa Yorishige to Kamakura. On the run and fighting to stay alive, Tokiyuki sets in motion his plan to reclaim his birthright.
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka IV: Shin Shou Meikyuu-hen

The fourth season of Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka. Intrepid adventurer Bell Cranel has leveled up, but he can’t rest on his dungeoneering laurels just yet. The Hestia Familia still has a long way to go before it can stand toe-to-toe with the other Familias of Orario — but before Bell can set out on his next mission, reports of a brutal murder rock the adventuring community! One of Bell’s trusted allies stands accused of the horrible crime, and it’s up to Bell and his friends to clear their name and uncover a nefarious plot brewing in the dungeon’s dark depths. (Source: Sentai Filmworks)

Guyangcheon betrayed the sect and became a demon under Cheonma. Living as a demon, he committed numerous evil deeds against his will under Cheonma's orders and ended up living a life filled with regret.
The Great Battle of Jeongma started by Cheonma. The long and hellish Great Battle of Jeongma came to an end due to Wisul-ah, who cut down Cheonma, who had even made the three great beings of Jeongpa kneel. Guyangcheon, who had been committing evil deeds as a demon, was captured by Jeongpa and tortured. While passing on information about the Demonic Cult to Wisul-ah with his last remaining conscience, he ended up dying due to Cheonma's prohibition.
However, for some reason, Guyangcheon regresses to the point where he first met Wisul-ah in the past. Realizing that the return was not a dream, Guyangcheon decides to live quietly so as not to do anything he would regret, but for some reason, the people he had bad ties with in his past life start to get entangled one by one, contrary to his intentions.
(Source: KakaoPage, translated)

Princess Enisha’s birth marks the start of the Hyperion Empire’s prophetic reign. With her unfathomably cute face and a ceaseless supply of loyal servants, life is pretty great for the baby princess. There’s just the small issue of her two psychotic-killer brothers and a war-hungry father who she must stop from driving the empire into ruin. Enisha’s got a lot on her plate, between the constant flood of assassins trying to kill her and those pesky memories of her past life. But she’s in no rush to return to being the powerful high mage of a magical kingdom. After all, being Hyperion’s one great hope certainly has its royal perks. It’s not easy being the empire’s beloved princess, but these subjects will just have to do.
(Source: Tappytoon)
